	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I made a <a href="http://youtu.be/X0_peGRCB14" class="postlink">youtube</a> vid on how I do it only a week or so ago...
<br />This is the connector I use from <a href="http://www.mouser.com/Search/ProductDetail.aspx?R=161-064SP-EXvirtualkey11180000virtualkey161-064SP-EX" class="postlink">Mouser</a>.
<br />It snaps right in to the hole where the RF jack sticks through, and has a similar grey color so it looks like it was almost meant to be there.
<br />The RF modulator is super easy to remove, I explain how I do it in the video.
<br />Do you already have the AV cord? If not I can find the one I buy off ebay and link you.
<br />Be sure to check the pinout of the AV cord, they are alll different it seems.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
